  Locus:
    Page: 236
    Verse: 18
Tags:
  - Health
---
Arise and accept an antidote to ward off old age and death; it is the
knowledge that all wealth and prosperity, all pleasures and enjoyments are
harmful to us unless devoted to the good of others; they tend only to
sicken and enervate our frames.
